Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.98,0:06:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.04,0:06:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.06,0:06:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.08,0:06:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.28,0:06:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You could be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.86,0:06:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.58,0:06:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You leave the body and you go, oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.93,0:06:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things with horns and tails hanging off of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.77,0:06:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to adapt to crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.34,0:06:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just talking to George about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.99,0:06:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,George wasn't aware of the news that now they're manufacturing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.87,0:07:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,bulletproof backpacks for kids to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Big sale on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.79,0:07:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They're selling them as fast as they can put them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you send your kid to school with a bulletproof backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.09,0:07:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That certainly is a change in society, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.59,0:07:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.77,0:07:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother used to tell me, don't take candy from strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.31,0:07:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a nice little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a candy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.93,0:07:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take candy from strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So at least I have a stranger who would offer me candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.39,0:07:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be scared out of my wits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.39,0:07:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody is up to no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.67,0:07:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.14,0:07:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we have Kev.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our backpacks for our children.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The next step will be people will realize they're going to need Kev.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.79,0:07:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our backpacks for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.73,0:07:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The next time we hear from the enemies of the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.73,0:07:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to realize we all better have Kev.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.31,0:08:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our clothes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,9-11 was only a shot across the bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.16,0:08:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask if we have permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.00,0:08:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,9-11 was only a shot across the bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.50,0:08:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not the grand finale, so we all may end up wearing, like I have on a Kevlar vest myself but it comes from a good store, wow, Dillard's, Dillard Kevlar vest, so that's class, class pays off, yeah, all right, accountability.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So then for the extent of crime, it's a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's acceptability.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.19,0:09:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We see this with the horrible story about the dog, what is it, dog fighting, what do you call that, dog fighting, stuff that the pit bull, yeah, that the basketball players have gotten into.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.17,0:09:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just part of that culture, but you can see the terrible response.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.99,0:09:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we have to put up with the various forms of pestilence, not like we did when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.71,0:09:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All the, all the great.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that scared everybody have disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Polio epidemic, diphtheria, typhoid, you know, where I lived, you would walk around the neighborhood and you would see the health department would put a warning, warning, diphtheria, warning, measles, worrying, chicken poop, chicken poops.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pooping cough, I was going to say not pooping cough, whooping cough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.91,0:09:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pooping cough, you cough so much you poop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.67,0:09:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whooping cough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.41,0:10:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All the diseases that everybody was scared to death of, polio, myelitis being one of the worst, no longer even exist, so that entire shift, that entire shift then of pestilence, pestilence, of course, wiped out the third of Europe, you know, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have natural calamities.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.42,0:10:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the negative depictions of God is part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.20,0:10:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In the chapter I'm writing right now, how did some religions get such negative depictions of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.75,0:10:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.41,0:10:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, God the punisher, God the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.93,0:10:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to kill infidels for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what kind of a God is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you don't need a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.35,0:10:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God gets off on your killing innocent children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.19,0:10:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It puts the devil out of business, unemployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.34,0:10:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How did all the demonic depictions of God arise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.61,0:10:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Did God?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.57,0:10:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,God is overjoyed that you kill innocent children, blow up a bustle out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.66,0:11:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How could such an evil God become sovereign?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.55,0:11:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the Mayan civilization and tear the heart out of maidens and hold them up while the heart is still beating and the blood is squirting down the steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All the demonic religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.85,0:11:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we realize there's two major classifications of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The satanic, which is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically evil, violence, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.05,0:11:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Luciferic, which is a substitution of falsehood for truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.52,0:11:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Those which are most evil demonstrate both.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.42,0:11:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They reverse truth to begin with and then have a satanic depiction of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.87,0:11:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So how could it be so prevalent?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Native American Indians, I believe, held such a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.67,0:11:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They saw God as the divinity of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.38,0:11:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And they saw the divinity and the spirits of the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.34,0:11:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So some people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:11:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people escaped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:12:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But the prevalence of God, the great punisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.13,0:12:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So God in the Old Testament, et cetera, is depicted in anthropomorphic terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.06,0:12:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jealous, vengeful, and angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes a lot of people turn away from religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.76,0:12:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't want to face a God that's as bad as an ordinary human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have jealousy, anger, and vengeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.64,0:12:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, how do you get to be God with the same character traits?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.91,0:12:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.65,0:12:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It dawned on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.37,0:12:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, why is such a negative depiction of God occurring, recurring over the millennia in different parts of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.85,0:12:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's because of natural disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.19,0:12:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Natural disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.53,0:12:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Earthquake and flood and fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.01,0:12:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how the gods must be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see if we've tracked it back correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.66,0:12:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.68,0:12:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tracked it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been tracked back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.46,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.72,0:13:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Zippity-doo-dah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.06,0:13:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever said that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.48,0:13:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a big collapse, a big mine collapses and earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.19,0:13:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an earthquake in Peru.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.74,0:13:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Earthquake in Peru.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.94,0:13:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing zillions of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.38,0:13:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have the tsunamis coming ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have the great plagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.47,0:13:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods must be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.25,0:13:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.34,0:13:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we rip out the heart of human sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.14,0:13:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Rip out the heart of a.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious that we have, this beautiful young virgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Rip out her beating heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.54,0:13:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe then God will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.94,0:13:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the angry God, then, is an animistic conceptualization of natural human disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.82,0:13:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And natural human disaster, you know, the whole principle of karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.98,0:13:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, how can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.32,0:13:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no explaining it logically.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:13:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you happen to be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.96,0:14:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you happen to be there at the time of the tsunami or the earthquake or the flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.47,0:14:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you're in San Francisco during the great earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.50,0:14:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the angry God would be, obviously, the conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.68,0:14:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're going to try and assuage this God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to assuage this God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can please him by killing all infidels.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just writing about that problem in a chapter of the book right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.58,0:14:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you assuage?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you assuage an angry God?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.37,0:14:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, you see, the negative arises from man's experience and a primitive interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.32,0:14:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A primitive interpretation based on natural disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to please this angry God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.63,0:14:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The angry God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.09,0:14:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So that he doesn't strike you dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.05,0:15:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy is on the street corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.87,0:15:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,His wife has run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.02,0:15:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gone bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a bad case of the hives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.63,0:15:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.07,0:15:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, why God?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.26,0:15:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, George.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.28,0:15:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something about you just pissing me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we share the fate of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.74,0:15:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's one thing in a way that, instead of being divisive, can be a bondingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.24,0:15:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A bondingness that, like ourselves, the people that we view as enemies, et cetera, are subject
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to the same vicissitudes, the same vicissitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.34,0:16:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's where the angry, vengeful God, the God of fear, you know, fear God, fear God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember a preacher saying that, fear God, and it made me shake all over because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was compulsively scrupulous to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.14,0:16:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All I needed was some guy telling me to fear God on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid to even think, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.27,0:16:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to watch what you looked at or what you might think, that you might have a negative
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,thought, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother would call you, come in for dinner now, and you might be angry at your mother
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for calling you in for dinner right in the middle of the stickball game, and you're scared
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.42,0:16:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to get an angry thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.11,0:16:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Best not to think at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.01,0:16:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Best not to even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.33,0:16:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you can avoid sin is to not be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.91,0:16:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Adaptational stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.33,0:16:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The stress of change, then, is constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big stress on the adrenal glands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.83,0:16:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Accountability and responsibility are critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.09,0:16:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,These people who lead lives of crime have no accountability, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of all of the complexity of the House of Mirrors we've talked about so far,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.17,0:17:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the media barrage, and the media barrage is quite serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.13,0:17:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The media barrage is intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.32,0:17:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It is incessant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.08,0:17:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes along with images, and you're being programmed all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.97,0:17:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being programmed all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.04,0:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The media barrage, then, you can't tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't tell integrity from non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.18,0:17:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't tell what's morality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.07,0:17:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is no real accountability, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.88,0:17:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The media barrage is sufficiently severe, especially bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.34,0:17:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloggerism is just, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.44,0:17:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't tell integrity from non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new disease of mankind in which it inflates your narcissistic ego with me being
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.56,0:18:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,out there in the YouTube and the MeTube, and being out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.90,0:18:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares what you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.60,0:18:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't give a rip what anybody thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.92,0:18:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.49,0:18:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody gets, blogger gets on there, they've got nothing else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.15,0:18:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.15,0:18:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't sleep, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.15,0:18:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They blogger, bloggerism all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.71,0:18:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.38,0:18:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It adds to the confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, eventually, discernment of truth from falsehood, the discernment … Eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.07,0:18:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens, eventually what happens, is the capacity to discern reality becomes injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm annoyed … annoyed with academia is not that they're teaching falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.90,0:18:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but that they're damaging the capacity to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.90,0:18:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I don't like about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.50,0:18:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're going to get it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,0.1.3.5.1.1.3.4.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.72,0:19:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the effect of it, you don't forget I practiced psychiatry 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.37,0:19:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I listened to the nuances and subtleties and what is unsaid beyond what is said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.59,0:19:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the capacity to discern reality has been seriously injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.65,0:19:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's see in what percentage of the present population.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.94,0:19:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In today's population, as a consequence of the media barrage,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.28,0:19:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to discern reality has been injured in over 40% of Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.67,0:19:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,45%.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.59,0:19:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,46%.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's 40?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.90,0:19:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's now at 45?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.48,0:19:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So 45% of the people who do nothing but witness this barrage, television, newspaper, magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.03,0:19:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and this programming and this falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.81,0:19:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget to bear false witness against your neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.50,0:20:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's breaking one of the great commandments.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.65,0:20:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And in today's world, it's routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.77,0:20:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's routine in politics to lie through your teeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,disparage little snide innuendos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.02,0:20:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So 40% of the people in the United States may have had it at one time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.06,0:20:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and now can't recognize truth even when you spell it out for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.39,0:20:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when you spell it out for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When you show them a picture like the first picture today,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.86,0:20:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,could there be anybody so defective in the upper story
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.56,0:20:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don't get that picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.25,0:20:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I like that picture is because it stunningly sits in your memory
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.81,0:20:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have any discussion about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.14,0:20:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just obvious what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.00,0:20:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Little red riding hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Little red riding hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.30,0:21:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have all these little red riding hoods in our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.56,0:21:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,40% of them in the United States can't understand truth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.94,0:21:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,even when you spell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.22,0:21:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Spell it out for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.75,0:21:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Spell it out for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Spell it out for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.32,0:21:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had it happen at a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.20,0:21:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Spent the whole lecture clarifying the nursing perception in essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.04,0:21:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end you get a sentence that you realize they didn't get even the slightest
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.76,0:21:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you were talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.46,0:21:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So that makes me look.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.92,0:21:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the ethos, the pathos, or the...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.48,0:21:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the speaker, the ethos, the message,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.04,0:21:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or the...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.82,0:21:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.38,0:21:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.60,0:21:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.04,0:21:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the media barrage then is on the one hand it brings us information never before available.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.97,0:21:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, be aware that the media is always programming you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.65,0:21:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always programming you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.27,0:21:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Always.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.60,0:21:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.24,0:22:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because first of all, they selected it to be on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.70,0:22:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That made it important right away, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.44,0:22:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how much time they give the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.02,0:22:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the music behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.72,0:22:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.36,0:22:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.50,0:22:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is sold with...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.97,0:22:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh look how...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.41,0:22:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.41,0:22:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for your eyes, your feet, new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.41,0:22:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at my new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.41,0:22:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.50,0:22:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is about sex, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.50,0:22:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to say to me, I'm so sick of being seduced and barraged by sexual images all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.89,0:22:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.89,0:22:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to watch the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.89,0:22:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A barrage of it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.89,0:22:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at the same time there's all the abstract images.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.23,0:22:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say that I'm a sex addict.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.23,0:22:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say that I'm a sex addict.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.58,0:22:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say that I'm a sex addict.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.58,0:22:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say that I'm a sex addict.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.58,0:22:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say that I'm a sex addict.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.58,0:22:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead is all about sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.65,0:23:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right so, just the fact that a thing is selected to be put on, then the image,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.25,0:23:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already been 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.03,0:23:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.03,0:23:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an important story.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.12,0:23:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,06.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.57,0:23:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because they put it up in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.91,0:23:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then if they repeat it over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.85,0:23:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you think, man, that's a super, super important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.80,0:23:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, nobody even knows
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.94,0:23:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to the Dow Jones average.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.30,0:23:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, most people have their money in savings,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.04,0:23:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but the news report doesn't even get around
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.58,0:23:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to what happened to the Dow today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.56,0:23:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're lucky, they'll say it dropped 60 points
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.34,0:23:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they quickly flash it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.04,0:23:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life savings is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.58,0:23:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.04,0:23:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she's busy telling you about...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.26,0:23:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.26,0:23:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one that they interview all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.98,0:23:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lady psychologist
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,who's supposed to be, I think, a sex therapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.78,0:23:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And when she comes on,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.98,0:23:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,she's got the biggest cleavage of anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.16,0:24:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a sex therapist, Dr. So-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.38,0:24:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to put them all to shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.82,0:24:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say to guys, if you really like those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.04,0:24:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,cover your wall with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.52,0:24:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the bedroom with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.52,0:24:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitchen with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,until you finally get off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.08,0:24:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen enough for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.68,0:24:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So TV's an endless burlesque show.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.72,0:24:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very comical.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.87,0:24:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But you realize then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.99,0:24:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're being programmed all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.02,0:24:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that you hear now
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.00,0:24:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is a program of one kind or another,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,programming you one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.80,0:24:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.53,0:24:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A media barrage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.63,0:24:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I wasn't doing what I'm doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.35,0:24:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to be a consultant to advertising companies
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.63,0:24:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because I can see how to improve ads right and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.75,0:25:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They're blowing all kinds of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.24,0:25:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I could show them how to quadruple
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.20,0:25:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the impact of their media.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.04,0:25:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So if there's a media barrage,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.02,0:25:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,then you really have to know how to manipulate the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.94,0:25:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the media is manipulated by 20-somethings.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.59,0:25:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of, what do you call these?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.85,0:25:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.20,0:25:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tickies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.66,0:25:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tickies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.26,0:25:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they call them tickies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.12,0:25:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the media barrage is by young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.39,0:25:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.61,0:25:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception versus essence, we said,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.43,0:25:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that is now being so injured
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.73,0:25:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that the capacity to even discern illusion from reality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.15,0:25:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is being lost even when you spell it out to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.17,0:25:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when you spell it out to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.76,0:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know that all of the above
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.72,0:25:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is being processed through the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.05,0:25:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.98,0:25:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud laid out an understanding of the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.56,0:25:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jung did it some from a different viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.82,0:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But Freud was really correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.98,0:26:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There is, at the basis of the human psyche,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.14,0:26:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.70,0:26:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the repressed animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.18,0:26:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to kill, to maim, to injure, to rape.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.80,0:26:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this guy that calibrated five.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.68,0:26:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a walking id.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.64,0:26:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire and the pleasure of killing,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.60,0:26:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which I've spoken about before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.40,0:26:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched dogs do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.40,0:26:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just kill, kill, kill, kill, kill
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.30,0:26:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sheer joy of killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.09,0:26:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, certain politicalization, brainwashing,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.55,0:26:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,knows how to access this id
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.51,0:26:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and release it under permission from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.27,0:26:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Under permission from God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.03,0:26:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you can become rapidly vicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.28,0:27:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because now you have permission for this id.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.53,0:27:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.03,0:27:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what balances the id is the superego, the conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.89,0:27:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you silence the conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.25,0:27:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and responsibility, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.35,0:27:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you can release the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.45,0:27:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the whole basis of frantic terrorism.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.59,0:27:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Goths, the busy Goths, the Vikings, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.43,0:27:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when they conquered people,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.71,0:27:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they killed them all and piled all the skulls up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.72,0:27:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Piled up the skulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.16,0:27:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They just killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.06,0:27:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When you beat somebody, you kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.52,0:27:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So the id, then, is the repressed reservoir
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.12,0:27:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the downside of one's animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.62,0:27:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And people don't want to look at the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.38,0:27:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the first things you have to do in psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.00,0:27:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is align the patient's superego with your sense of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.44,0:27:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they can face the fact that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.84,0:28:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.42,0:28:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.46,0:28:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.52,0:28:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.76,0:28:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then somebody gets a promotion above you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.98,0:28:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you know, the patient's talking about this, that,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.34,0:28:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.98,0:28:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And now what do you really feel about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.44,0:28:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And now what do you really feel about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.64,0:28:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all of a sudden you begin to shake
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.30,0:28:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel nervous and shame to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.32,0:28:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you really feel about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.30,0:28:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to kill him, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.88,0:28:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.44,0:28:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You really unconsciously want to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.84,0:28:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy who passes you and sticks his thumb figure out,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.03,0:28:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.11,0:28:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.50,0:28:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here want to kill that SOB?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.84,0:28:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody thinks he should live?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.68,0:28:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.98,0:28:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes by, gives you the finger, he should die.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.38,0:28:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,His car should roll over in the next century.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.58,0:28:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, in the basis of the id, it thinks of killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.10,0:28:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks of killing others.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.51,0:29:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have a religion that releases the id
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.73,0:29:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and eliminates the superego,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.56,0:29:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and it says God is on the side of your id,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.72,0:29:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we're battling now for the survival of Western civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.36,0:29:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is the God of the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.97,0:29:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of the id is the enemy of Western civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.39,0:29:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will go to heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.17,0:29:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or you'll have endless hotsy-totsies,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.92,0:29:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,72 of them or 77,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.62,0:29:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as a reward for releasing your id,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.24,0:29:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,releasing your id and killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.04,0:29:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the superego then balances the pressure of the id,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.18,0:29:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in the animal instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.39,0:29:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ego is, in Freudian terminology,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.01,0:30:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not spiritual terminology, Freudian terminology,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.75,0:30:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the strength to balance the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.13,0:30:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A healthy ego is able to handle and accept and repress,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.01,0:30:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,handle instincts,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.03,0:30:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and not go into a guilt trip about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.41,0:30:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the ego that is aligned with what we call reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.75,0:30:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the person's reality testing,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.72,0:30:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.62,0:30:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the instinctual urges against guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.84,0:30:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the attack of the superego.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.40,0:30:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you allow the superego to become hypertrophied,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.24,0:30:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up with scrupulosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.22,0:30:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up with guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.72,0:30:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you eventually end up with depression
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.28,0:30:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because you judge,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.10,0:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you judge against yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.84,0:30:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I have been so evil as to have been,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.96,0:30:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,feel angry at my mother for wanting me to quit playing stickball
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.64,0:30:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and come in and wash my hands for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.44,0:30:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the balance then.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.08,0:31:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Freudian ego is the capacity to balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.46,0:31:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The repressed unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.48,0:31:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and people like Adolf Hitler, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.54,0:31:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the great dictators have learned how to regiment the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.44,0:31:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The id can be silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.64,0:31:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but it can be silenced by the herd instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.94,0:31:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The hanging, a group of people hangs somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.30,0:31:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fact that it's a group,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.90,0:31:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't feel guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.46,0:31:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If one person did it or a couple did,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.02,0:31:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but so the superego dissolves in the herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.27,0:31:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a basic principle of Freudian psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.33,0:31:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If everybody says it's all right to kill them,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.11,0:31:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's okay to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.65,0:31:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You, by yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.02,0:31:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would not be able to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.02,0:31:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the herd instinct gives the superego,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.30,0:31:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you permission to own,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.08,0:31:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.18,0:31:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how you get great words.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.06,0:32:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.14,0:32:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of collectivist,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.11,0:32:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of collectivist psychology,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.95,0:32:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the Nazi party was called the National Socialist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.45,0:32:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan was a divine imperialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.15,0:32:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Communism was, I don't know, workers unite and release your chains,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.57,0:32:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the hateful capitalists, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.70,0:32:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you can see how man is now manipulated in group form
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.56,0:32:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by manipulating the superego, and you say, it's good to do this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.88,0:32:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to hate that, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.45,0:32:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So the healthy person with a sense of reality done
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.95,0:32:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,has a balance between their conscience, their instinctual.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.93,0:32:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have to deny.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.45,0:32:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So in psychoanalysis, you stop denying primitive instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.88,0:32:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.84,0:32:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just assume kill them, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.99,0:33:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the net effect of this is via the endocrine glands,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.09,0:33:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said, the stress hormones,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.57,0:33:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it ends up affecting brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.17,0:33:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we showed from the brain physiology chart
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.07,0:33:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from before that your level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.55,0:33:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now affects your brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.46,0:33:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for half the population
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.22,0:33:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to comprehend spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.60,0:33:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.00,0:33:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.30,0:33:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They can only understand the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.04,0:33:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian world of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.42,0:33:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no comprehension of the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.56,0:33:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand context.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.90,0:33:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand context.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.94,0:33:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it right for the government to spy on your e-mails
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.78,0:33:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to overseas suspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.80,0:33:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on whether you're at war or not at war, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.72,0:33:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes all the difference in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.82,0:33:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes all the difference in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.15,0:34:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at war, then certain things,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.26,0:34:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you're not at war.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.48,0:34:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's naivete to deny, to ignore context,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.10,0:34:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to ignore context.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.52,0:34:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best example of context influencing morality
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.84,0:34:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is situational ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.38,0:34:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, no, no, what's right and wrong is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.52,0:34:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It all depends on the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.32,0:34:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Every courtroom case is a case of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.00,0:34:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the situation whereby you pulled the trigger, et cetera?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.26,0:34:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you being threatened?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.34,0:34:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you think you were?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.16,0:34:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought I was being threatened,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.60,0:34:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn't really a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.05,0:34:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only a hamburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.90,0:34:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to get out of his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.45,0:34:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that guy's an idiot with a cop standing there with a gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.69,0:34:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and he reaches in his pocket for a hamburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.07,0:34:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.96,0:34:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you expect the cop to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.62,0:34:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,stand there and wait until he gets killed first?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.49,0:34:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.79,0:35:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, we know in every courtroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.67,0:35:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at the context,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.41,0:35:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the context in which this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.23,0:35:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.61,0:35:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the motivation?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.66,0:35:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that 50% of identification of suspects is erroneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.04,0:35:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether they call it personal ID or what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.44,0:35:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.54,0:35:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.70,0:35:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.55,0:35:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.89,0:35:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Eyewitnessing, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.85,0:35:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Statistically, 50% of the people they finger from the lineup is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.19,0:35:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.71,0:35:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.86,0:35:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the guy that did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.98,0:35:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.28,0:35:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We know from that project,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.67,0:35:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to think of the name of the project last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.01,0:35:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when DNA came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.75,0:35:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They went through the death row of the prisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.70,0:35:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people did they let out?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.16,0:35:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.45,0:35:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.94,0:35:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.72,0:36:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the name of that project?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.09,0:36:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the crew that was in the famous, whatchamacallit, murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.29,0:36:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.23,0:36:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocence Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.15,0:36:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.77,0:36:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.57,0:36:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.95,0:36:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,DNA went out and reexamined all the guys in the death row.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.27,0:36:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget the total number of people who were innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.37,0:36:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,195.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.49,0:36:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a sizable number.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.15,0:36:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A sizable number.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.09,0:36:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Society wants revenge, and therefore it's very willing to believe anything negative
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.97,0:36:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to get even, seeking revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.61,0:36:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was a very worthwhile enterprise, and it's sort of scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.43,0:36:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of the reasons that I've always been against capital punishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.73,0:36:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if you're mistaken, you can't correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.11,0:36:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who would want that on their conscience?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.35,0:36:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to be the judge, condemning somebody to death, and then find out later
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.84,0:36:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with DNA evidence he wasn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.70,0:36:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how could you live with your own, I would spend the rest of my life, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.69,0:37:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,assuaging guilt and penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.01,0:37:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm against the death penalty for one reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.21,0:37:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only is it, in my view, uncouth, but you can't correct the mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.01,0:37:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot correct the mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.81,0:37:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the effect then is on brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.28,0:37:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So all this media barrage programming is affecting your brain physiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.20,0:37:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's affecting your endocrine system, and your cortisone,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.52,0:37:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and stress hormones.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.44,0:37:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So while they're pounding away on you, your brain physiology is going through stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.88,0:37:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Your adrenal glands, which sit on top of the adrenal, and put out cortisone,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.54,0:37:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,put out cortisone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.61,0:37:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The happy brain, the happy brain is putting out endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.75,0:37:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Endorphins make you feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.31,0:37:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the happy person, then, his brain is putting out endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.53,0:38:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The person living below 200 is constantly under stress, so he's putting out adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.75,0:38:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,ACTH and stress, cortisone, stress hormones.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.20,0:38:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So this all affects our brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.72,0:38:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, we did an interesting program on music.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.71,0:38:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Influencing all of this, overall, is also the exposure to music, the arts, and aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.33,0:38:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that people who are spiritually capable, or adaptable, or equipped, or to whom it comes natural,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.35,0:38:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,very often, usually, have a very...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.33,0:38:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,extensive exposure to music, the arts, and aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.32,0:38:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Music, and the arts, and the aesthetics influences brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.36,0:38:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also influences neuronal connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.70,0:38:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As you're aware, the human brain is constantly producing thousands of neurons, all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.41,0:38:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless they connect up and are put into the circuit, they decremate, and then a whole new batch comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.37,0:39:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So an exposure to music, religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.75,0:39:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetics, et cetera, and humor, humor, et cetera, goodwill, influences the way the neuronal connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.63,0:39:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I not infrequently get something from my mother, what can I do to make sure that my child
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.63,0:39:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,devolves their spiritual capacity?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.63,0:39:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was telling them, the best thing you can do is expose them to aesthetics, to ballet, to the theater, to opera, to the arts, to nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.63,0:39:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And develop a love for music.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.76,0:39:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was telling them, the best thing you can do is expose them to aesthetics, to ballet, to the theater, to opera, to the arts, to nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.80,0:39:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was telling them, the best thing you can do is expose them to aesthetics, to love, and a synchronicity with beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.08,0:39:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is, what? Saturday?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.34,0:39:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thursday, I think, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.34,0:39:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a crew that's going to do a program on music for some PBS thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.34,0:39:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And all they wanted to do was have me discuss the impact of music on the persons overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.66,0:39:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact on society.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.17,0:40:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the crime rate amongst people who are raised,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.17,0:40:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the crime rate amongst people who are raised,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.17,0:40:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,have exposure to religion plus aesthetics, the crime rate is practically zero. The crime
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.98,0:40:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,rate amongst people with a heavy exposure to aesthetics and the love of animals and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.90,0:40:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of nature is practically zero. Practically zero crime rate. Practically zero crime rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.75,0:40:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that amazing? Yeah, but you got to listen to Wagner and Beethoven and all that. So a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.00,0:40:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,child brought up listening to the Overture to Lohengrin. In my family, everybody was
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.62,0:40:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,musical, you see. My grandmother played classical music all the time. She was pregnant with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.74,0:40:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,my father. And people laughed at her as an ignorant old Irish lady, you know. And she
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.32,0:41:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,said, you'll see, you'll see. And it turned out he was a great musician, yeah. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.88,0:41:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,she used to read me Shakespeare.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.48,0:41:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So classical music and Shakespeare. And then Saturday afternoon, the Metropolitan Opera
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.96,0:41:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would come from New York City and Milton Krauss would explain the opera. And pretty soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.08,0:41:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you're really caught up in the Nibelung Ring and looking for the Lohengrin.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.38,0:41:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes intrinsic. And of course, all this is having an effect not only on the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.02,0:41:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,physiology, but actually on the brain anatomy, the brain neurology. The neurons are actually
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.76,0:41:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,connected to the brain. So in the presence of beautiful music, in their absence, these
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.34,0:41:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,two neurons don't connect. In the presence of it, the thrill and pleasure of it, these
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.86,0:41:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,neurons say, oh, we're worthwhile, we're what you want, and they connect up. So you progressively
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.64,0:42:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,become more spiritually aligned in your brain physiology. So what can you do for your children?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.09,0:42:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can teach them appreciation for beauty in all of its forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.37,0:42:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to go to all the art galleries. You get to see all the great ballet. And in the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.94,0:42:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,town, I lived in Milwaukee, the great artists would come through. And of course, you went
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.46,0:42:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to see them because they were rare. Sadler-Wells Ballet or New York City Ballet, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.07,0:42:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,would come through. You went to see it. If you live in New York City, you never go to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.23,0:42:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,see it. Why? Because it's there all the time. You can go anytime. If you live in New York
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.70,0:42:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,City because it's there all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.22,0:42:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get to go to all the art galleries. You get to see all the great ballet. And in
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.40,0:42:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can go anytime, you never go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.28,0:42:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask somebody who lived all their life in New York City,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.58,0:42:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,have you ever been to the top of the Empire State Building?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.58,0:42:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll say, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.82,0:42:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if they have a visitor from out of town,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.56,0:42:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then they go to see the top of the Empire State Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.66,0:42:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.94,0:42:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's available all the time, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.64,0:43:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the best thing to do is live in a city where these things are highly valued
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.46,0:43:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're not there all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.80,0:43:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so when they come through, they're an occasion and worth going to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.55,0:43:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Appreciation for music, the arts, and aesthetics,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.87,0:43:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for ballet and the theater arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.86,0:43:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,These phenomena, the brain barrage,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.26,0:43:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,results in a certain amount of what's called imprinting.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.94,0:43:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Imprinting.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.12,0:43:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how you get brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.81,0:43:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The program has already happened to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.09,0:43:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and by the time you decide you don't want to get involved in that,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.63,0:43:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.99,0:43:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.85,0:43:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing that gives things meaning and significance and importance is framing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.41,0:43:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the media, what we're talking about is the framing is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.01,0:43:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that the media has selected it to report in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.65,0:43:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the sequence in which these things are presented to you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.77,0:44:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will have a different impact on your brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.87,0:44:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In a certain sequence, a certain image will disappear and not be recallable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.41,0:44:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In a different sequence, it highly has a great impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.65,0:44:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the programming of the media, then, is profoundly significant
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.65,0:44:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and profoundly affecting the capacity to recognize a reality in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.72,0:44:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We, of course, are more sophisticated people,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.36,0:44:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,are aware of context versus content.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.82,0:44:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Context is nonlinear, and content is linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.70,0:44:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether a thing is a crime or not and how serious it is depends on the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.06,0:44:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The context versus the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.78,0:44:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Content.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.23,0:44:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of all the other favorable things is a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.07,0:44:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.06,0:44:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.99,0:44:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it's extremely important.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.31,0:44:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I think humor is as important as any of the other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.05,0:44:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.43,0:44:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humor has a healing effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.31,0:44:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Humor, if you do the arm on it, makes you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.98,0:45:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Humor points out the ambiguities,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.42,0:45:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and it points out very often the ambiguity between the content and the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.32,0:45:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.80,0:45:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And how you sometimes see the two end up really the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.62,0:45:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.06,0:45:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the intention is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.96,0:45:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think humor has a tremendously healing effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.70,0:45:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've mentioned that in previous lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.72,0:45:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And some people have written books on how they recovered from grave illnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.18,0:45:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by just employing nothing but humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.40,0:45:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All they did was laugh all the time and get every funny movie they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.74,0:45:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So humor releases endorphins,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.80,0:45:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,releases...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.44,0:45:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a positive brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.40,0:45:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And humor is based so much on ambiguity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.26,0:45:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The contrast between what is said and what we know really goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.44,0:45:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it makes us laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.98,0:45:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the way I think cultural...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.58,0:45:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call it between classes?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.80,0:46:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.84,0:46:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The natural way is for it to dissolve through humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.89,0:46:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if women do that much, but men do.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.99,0:46:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're always kidding each other about...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.53,0:46:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,About their background or the world I grew up anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.47,0:46:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Always kid each other about their own background.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.59,0:46:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's all very good humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.57,0:46:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've mentioned before, you know, the guy that had a license plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.94,0:46:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I would pass him every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.06,0:46:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The license plate said, kiss me, I'm Irish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.66,0:46:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, kiss me, I'm Polish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.22,0:46:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiss me, I'm Polish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.94,0:46:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was so hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.24,0:46:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So men have learned in the workplace, in the workplace,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.80,0:46:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to joke about it and include it in a non-insulting way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.56,0:46:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And sort of an endearing kind of a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.35,0:46:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we couldn't run this brewery without you Polacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.29,0:46:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we couldn't run a brewery without the Polacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.41,0:46:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Milwaukee, Milwaukee, you couldn't run a brewery without the Polacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.05,0:46:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.01,0:46:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So then it became okay to be who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.55,0:47:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So through humor, it has a healing effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.97,0:47:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's okay to be who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.63,0:47:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that just in between the sexes,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.45,0:47:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if you take out the snot,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.17,0:47:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the denied negativity of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.21,0:47:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,men and women learn to get along each other extremely well through humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.52,0:47:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just talking this morning about men are from,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.89,0:47:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,where are men from?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.10,0:47:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Men are from Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.97,0:47:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Women are from Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.31,0:47:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, heck, I thought we were, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.38,0:47:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Men are from Mars and women are from Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.78,0:47:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And men tend to lose, I don't know about women,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.59,0:47:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but men tend to lose track of that knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.75,0:47:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you haven't read it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.05,0:47:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's demanded that you read it to become a mature human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.03,0:47:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the fact that men and women see things differently
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.19,0:48:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,explains all the arguments.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.11,0:48:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you understand it, you can look at any argument and you'll see,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.85,0:48:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that they tend to see things differently than men.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.30,0:48:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The man will look at it, cold heart intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.88,0:48:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's looking at it from emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.12,0:48:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.10,0:48:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what about the cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.26,0:48:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The comfort of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.58,0:48:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying, we already got three cantaloupes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.64,0:48:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you brought another one home.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.80,0:48:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was afraid that wouldn't be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.32,0:48:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, I'll eat a cantaloupe all week long.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.53,0:48:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To the man, reason and logic, you got two cantaloupes,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.63,0:48:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,why do you need a third cantaloupe?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.89,0:48:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're on sale and, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.93,0:48:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you get that the woman's intention is domestic,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.91,0:49:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,she wants everybody to be provided for and happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.55,0:49:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll say, why are you washing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.51,0:49:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They're sheets, you just washed them yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.44,0:49:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's a new day and she wants them to be fluffy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.66,0:49:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The man's intellect says, hell, they were just washed the day before.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.12,0:49:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's that ambiance of the feminine as the provider, as the nurturer that,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.61,0:49:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore what has to do with survival as she sees it from that picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.48,0:49:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And the man is only looking, you know, at like it's at the office practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.86,0:49:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's saying, we got two bananas, why do you need a third one?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.04,0:49:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, the humor then.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.33,0:49:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody has to read that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.29,0:49:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't want to hear any complaints unless you've read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.90,0:50:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.04,0:50:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was still in practice, I used to have all of my patients who were having marital problems read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.90,0:50:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And everyone said it's just, oh, wow, made it all, oh, I see, I see, oh, oh, I see how it looks to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.56,0:50:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.57,0:50:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So on top of all this, we call all this indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.61,0:50:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily purposeful indoctrination, but you're constantly being indoctrinated and programmed by the human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.24,0:50:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes through as memes, repetitive quotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.56,0:50:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, everybody hates Bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.90,0:50:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to hate Bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.26,0:50:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.86,0:50:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.51,0:50:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So memes then are repetitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.45,0:50:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Repetitious phrases that become quoted so often that they're accepted as though they were truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.81,0:51:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They're accepted as though they were truth just by sheer repetition.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.35,0:51:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that all the time in the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.53,0:51:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it in the evening news.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.12,0:51:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.34,0:51:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The meme then is a way of becoming programmed and indoctrinated without realizing you're becoming indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.46,0:51:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's such a constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.70,0:51:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's such a common phrase.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.66,0:51:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid whatchamacallits.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.24,0:51:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid white men or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.96,0:51:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a meme after a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.61,0:51:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind all of this and all of these things we've talked about so far is intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.55,0:51:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are energized by intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.11,0:51:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're programmed or not depends on the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.95,0:51:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the intention of the person who writes, I call them snides.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.30,0:51:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The blogger, bloggerdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.76,0:51:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.16,0:51:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have anything to do with bloggerdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.61,0:51:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.11,0:51:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to work one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.99,0:51:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to know how to work one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.14,0:52:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I avoid bloggerdom because so much of the intention is so snide, so vicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.70,0:52:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This shift of a word to try and make the person look worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.73,0:52:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just say you hate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.29,0:52:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just say that you hate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.23,0:52:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.69,0:52:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the intention then slants.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.79,0:52:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,These memes tend to be repetitious to the point of dangerousness, dangerousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.24,0:52:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, our main enemy of this, our Western culture in the world today,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.28,0:52:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,have become experts at propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.96,0:52:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they're following precisely exactly the same as Nazi Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.61,0:52:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,following exactly the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.73,0:52:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Protocol of the Elders of Zion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.21,0:52:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Picturing the enemy as vicious-looking, making them look like rats, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.45,0:53:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the programming is going on visually, visually pictorially.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.86,0:53:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind all this is the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.78,0:53:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Discernment versus naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.44,0:53:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To merely know the things we've been talking about gives you greater discernment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.84,0:53:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because you realize that the mind unaided is naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.40,0:53:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.90,0:53:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.76,0:53:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Unaided.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.40,0:53:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.52,0:53:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,People write me nasty blogs once in a while about that and ridicule it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.11,0:53:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If they got what I was saying, they wouldn't have written that blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.69,0:53:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind unaided is so dominated by the structure of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.42,0:53:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot discern perception from essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.74,0:53:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And one thing that brings it up, brings up one's level to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.63,0:53:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it's reality is narcissism versus spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.63,0:54:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism is so interested in just dominating with its own viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.28,0:54:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And spirituality begins to seek truth for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.28,0:54:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Seek truth for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.00,0:54:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So the antidote to all of these things is spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.98,0:54:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer can be quick and short.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.48,0:54:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God or no God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.68,0:54:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You say there's no God, you just had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.62,0:54:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.72,0:54:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.72,0:54:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,For this time of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.09,0:54:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And God makes all the difference in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.13,0:54:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether a person, you know, holds that God is a hypothetical likelihood,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.06,0:54:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera, is completely different than negating.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.89,0:54:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.35,0:54:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So skepticism is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.31,0:54:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheism is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.07,0:54:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself was a devout agnostic for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.69,0:54:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an atheist and I got more sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.01,0:54:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I became an agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.23,0:54:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Became an agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.27,0:54:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So God or no God then.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.59,0:54:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.33,0:55:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . is the overall context in which all of this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.13,0:55:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The House of Mirrors looks completely different when it is illuminated by the light of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.22,0:55:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So this morning we just thought we'd take a quick tour through a portion of the House
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.89,0:55:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of Mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.57,0:55:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it in small doses.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.03,0:55:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it in small doses.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.27,0:55:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we're going to have a break and resume at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.77,0:55:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.01,0:55:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to resume it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.21,0:55:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A to.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.73,0:56:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,o'clock. Here's all my little fellas, all my little friends. We understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.93,0:56:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway. Let's see, where were we? Anybody remember? Where am I? I guess we must still
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.73,0:56:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,be in the house of mirrors. Is this the way to truth? Oh, looks false to me. Oh, I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.18,0:56:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that was true. Sorry. Oh, we finished 116. Okay. Okay, somebody knows where we are. The
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.74,0:56:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,human dilemma, you know. You see how exquisitely difficult it really is when you look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.91,0:57:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,objectively. We're all walking miracles that we survived this far, aren't we? All the deception
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.74,0:57:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and illusions and the brainwashing and not to mention wars and crashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.44,0:57:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Now, the human dilemma. All right. So, one's alignment with truth. One's alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.70,0:57:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with truth means that at every intersection, you choose that which is true. And constantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.03,0:57:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if you constantly choose that which is true, you will end up in a completely different
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.47,0:57:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension than people who constantly choose what is false because they end up actually
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.93,0:57:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in an alternate reality. It is really not the same reality, which helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.52,0:57:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps you with judgmentalism because you realize the way you experience the world is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.92,0:57:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not the way that person is experiencing it. What seems to you blatant and obvious truth
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.64,0:58:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to them is falsehood. What seems logical and sensible doesn't even cross their mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.28,0:58:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it gives you, you know, the Lord said to be forgiving towards all. And to be forgiving
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.78,0:58:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on how you see the person. So, when you see the person differently, you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.38,0:58:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,judging them. Then you realize they live in a different sense of reality, a different
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.90,0:58:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,world than you do. And you can't judge them by your standards because they can't even
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.90,0:58:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehend your standards. They cannot comprehend your standards. So, we consider mercy, mercy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.71,0:58:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially being merciful towards the weak and innocent as a virtue. There's a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.22,0:58:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,other culture which threatens our own existence, actually, which sees it exactly the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.34,0:58:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemptible weakness. Contemptible weakness. And therefore, you're deserving of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.59,0:59:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. So, your alignment then has a very powerful effect on how you experience the world, what
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.40,0:59:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you interpret as truth or valuable, all your value judgments are coming out of your alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.44,0:59:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that alignment, we're seeking God versus materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.98,0:59:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Materialism. The spiritual versus the material. God versus the worship of money and wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.40,0:59:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And worldly power. Worldly power. I don't know what people want worldly power for. It
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.61,0:59:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to me like a terrible nuisance. But a lot of people will do anything to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.07,0:59:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mean, I think it would be a terrible drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.52,0:59:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.52,0:59:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Worldly power. But many people, you know, and today's liberator is tomorrow's dictator.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.78,1:00:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's written in italics in my new book. Tomorrow's liberator is tomorrow's dictator.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.61,1:00:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's liberator is tomorrow's dictator. You know any cases where that's not true? Cuba.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.18,1:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world. Today's liberator is tomorrow's dictator. Yeah? All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.51,1:00:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I say? Cesar Chavez? No, no. To me, he's more of a comedian. A comedian.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.76,1:00:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A comedian. I can see our Hollywood luminaries running over to embrace him. It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.02,1:00:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So on top of all this stack of things that you have to deal with in this house of mirrors,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.02,1:00:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got biologic factors and hormonal drives.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.02,1:00:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hormonal drives driving you crazy. All young men are driven crazy by testosterone.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.55,1:01:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The instinctual drives. Yeah. Testosterone is the seed of madness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.06,1:01:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is, you know. The curse of being a male is that you're driven by testosterone,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.22,1:01:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which allows you no rest. Allows you no rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.12,1:01:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus it raises the level of like an elephant in musk. See?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.28,1:01:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A number of males are like elephants in musk. Very combative. Very hostile to each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.28,1:01:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And mounting a female is the only thing on their mind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.89,1:01:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes your life simple. There's only one thing you're interested in.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.86,1:02:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.94,1:02:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It satisfies you at least for an hour maybe. A couple of hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.49,1:02:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. All right. Sublimation. You know the Freudian psychology talks about the negative instincts,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.64,1:02:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the negative drives, to sublimate them instead of acting them out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.86,1:02:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can take the energy of a lesser drive and put it into constructive ends
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.86,1:02:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome evil for the sake of good.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.41,1:02:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.55,1:02:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sublimation then means you find an outlet to release some of the pressure of a certain drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.55,1:02:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Creativity is one, for instance. The instinctual drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.58,1:02:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Creativity tends to diminish the preoccupation with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.74,1:02:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So sublimation versus acting out means to socialize that particular instinctual drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.74,1:03:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your anger and your resentment in a constructive way to like rebuild a better way of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.74,1:03:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.74,1:03:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of hating this way of solving a thing, doing a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.74,1:03:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is you build a better mousetrap, find a better way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.97,1:03:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sublimation is a Freudian psychotherapy versus acting out.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.45,1:03:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire for control is so endemic and so endemic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.74,1:03:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Power over others, dominance, hegemony, the whole alpha male syndrome.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.96,1:03:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.30,1:03:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we won't even talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.17,1:03:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he tries to make, let's say you want to make America wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.36,1:03:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find examples of American hegemony.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.36,1:03:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, his doctrine is hegemonous because he's trying to have his doctrine prevail
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.58,1:03:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and be dominant over others.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.58,1:04:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the desire for control is in people who put down wanting to control.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.74,1:04:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.94,1:04:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire for control, power over others, people seem to get a great deal out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.54,1:04:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always considered it, frankly, a nuisance to control other people
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.54,1:04:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because then they become your responsibility and you've got all kinds of karmic liability, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.67,1:04:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just as soon everybody drive their own golf cart, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.67,1:04:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.67,1:04:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to push them off the green and get one up on them, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.67,1:04:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.67,1:04:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire for control.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.67,1:04:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see how this is like an obsession with many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.67,1:04:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, in marital relationships, who's going to be the one that controls, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.67,1:04:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we see this movie or that movie?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.67,1:04:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,People get a sense of power out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.67,1:04:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's sort of a narcissistic self-indulgence to always want to control people and situations
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.74,1:04:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of riding with the . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.74,1:05:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes it's a conflict, an ethical conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.89,1:05:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Should one try to take control and, in your view of it, make it better or just turn it over to God?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.89,1:05:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find, pragmatically speaking, turning it over to God, it works well.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.89,1:05:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.89,1:05:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call those things you call go-arounds, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.09,1:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Sedona, there's a big discussion now about putting in go-arounds instead of . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.09,1:05:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.09,1:05:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.09,1:05:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.09,1:05:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.09,1:05:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.09,1:05:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.44,1:05:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.44,1:05:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.44,1:05:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.33,1:05:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.33,1:05:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.33,1:05:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.33,1:05:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.33,1:05:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.33,1:05:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.46,1:05:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.46,1:05:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.46,1:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.46,1:05:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.46,1:05:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.46,1:05:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.46,1:05:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.46,1:05:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.46,1:05:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.46,1:05:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.46,1:05:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.46,1:05:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.46,1:05:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.46,1:05:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.46,1:06:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.46,1:06:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.46,1:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.46,1:06:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.46,1:06:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.46,1:06:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.46,1:06:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.46,1:06:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.46,1:06:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.96,1:06:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The go-around, go-around, that's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.02,1:06:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the way people drive in South America.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.58,1:06:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, South America is hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.54,1:06:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll be a six-lane, you know, down in the tip of Argentina.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.64,1:06:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.96,1:06:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Buenos Aires.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.22,1:06:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's like Paris, and there's this huge boulevard, huge fountains, gorgeous.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.88,1:06:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then about six or eight lanes wide on both sides of the boulevard, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.66,1:06:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And people drive like a mad fiend.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.82,1:06:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no arterial stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.02,1:06:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So at every intersection is who's going to get through first.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.30,1:06:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And when people drive there, they drive real tight in these little cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.00,1:06:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one arm goes out the window like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.28,1:06:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.85,1:06:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see all these cars, all these arms are out there, and they're just packed real tight,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.17,1:06:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,these little buzzy cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.63,1:07:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly any clearance between the cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.87,1:07:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And no arterial stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.53,1:07:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.83,1:07:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.49,1:07:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings up all your adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.88,1:07:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the herd instinct is how is the end of the superego.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.22,1:07:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The superego is one's conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.32,1:07:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And one's conscience is soluble within a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.22,1:07:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The lynch mob, one or two guys on their own can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.94,1:07:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if a dozen guys join you, now it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.02,1:07:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Hitler's proposition.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.84,1:07:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In Europe, it would have been rejected as totally outrageous by a few people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.72,1:07:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you get a whole crowd,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.44,1:07:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Seagal, Seagal, Seagal.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.27,1:07:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can bomb Britain.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.75,1:07:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.83,1:07:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Invade foreign countries.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.41,1:07:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's perfectly okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.23,1:08:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfectly okay if the whole mob does it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.49,1:08:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the herd instinct, then, is how large segments of society shift 180 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.56,1:08:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you look at the history,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.02,1:08:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the development of some civilizations.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.98,1:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I can't believe, I can't believe they could have done a 180 on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.93,1:08:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They did a 180 because under propaganda and a charismatic leader,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.21,1:08:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the herd instinct takes over.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.53,1:08:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And people will perpetrate extremely horrible acts if everybody's doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.16,1:08:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of all this, we have a desire for acceptance and approval from others.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.81,1:08:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody has to agree with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.93,1:08:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That, of course, is a narcissistic orientation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.26,1:08:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire for approval.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.08,1:09:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You reach a point where you really have no interest in whether people approve of you or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.97,1:09:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just part of your information, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.68,1:09:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,whether something is being accepted or approved of.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.98,1:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's of no personal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.06,1:09:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.82,1:09:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as you evolve spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.24,1:09:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need any, progressively, less and less to the final, you don't need anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.59,1:09:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.63,1:09:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At a certain level of consciousness, you don't want anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.72,1:09:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to keep on breathing in and out?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.02,1:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know that I really care about it that much.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.40,1:09:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It either happens or it doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.36,1:09:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.94,1:09:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So letting go of people's desire for approval means that you're less controllable.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.22,1:09:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people want to control you with their approval.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.26,1:09:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Or their disapproval.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.53,1:10:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And desire for acceptance and approval, you know, runs a great many people all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.13,1:10:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All they're looking for is approval from somebody out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.75,1:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To counteract that, there's a capacity for gratitude and thankfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.86,1:10:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've mentioned that before in lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.02,1:10:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you just thank a clerk, thank anybody, a workman who comes to your house, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.34,1:10:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,until you're satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.38,1:10:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell them what a great job it was, and how much you appreciate it, and give them
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.16,1:10:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a genuine, not a fake thank, a real thank you, people drop their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.86,1:10:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They go, well, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.86,1:10:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so just thanking people.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.05,1:10:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's just sort of like turning over black beetles so they can walk on their feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.01,1:10:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanking people and having gracious attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.03,1:10:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could contextualize this whole.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.41,1:11:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The social milieu, this whole way of relating to society, as grace, graciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.30,1:11:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the shortcut, then, to spiritual reality is to develop the habit of being gracious
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.92,1:11:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,towards all of life and all of its expressions all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.03,1:11:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The person slams their brake on, and you rear end them.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.82,1:11:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What should happen next?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.85,1:11:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do next?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.37,1:11:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.39,1:11:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, I'm sorry this happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.39,1:11:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the first person, the average person would say, well, it was your fault to slam
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.22,1:11:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,them on the brakes, you son of a bitch, and I'm suing you, too, goddammit.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.22,1:11:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly turn them into an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.73,1:11:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.76,1:11:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He slammed his brakes on, gave you no warning.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.76,1:12:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And, however, what you do is you apologize for the awkwardness of the situation, for
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.11,1:12:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the awkwardness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.11,1:12:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to demean yourself by, you know, crying.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.11,1:12:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to say, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.11,1:12:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.11,1:12:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.11,1:12:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace doesn't mean to demean yourself and become a lick-spittle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.11,1:12:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It really means, you know, to apologize for the inevitabilities of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.11,1:12:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only drive so many miles when a dented fender is likely to surface on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.21,1:12:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you do is you tell the person who backs into you, you know, in the parking lot,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.34,1:12:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,dent your fender.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.34,1:12:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell them, look, don't get upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.34,1:12:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, don't get upset about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.34,1:12:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You got insurance.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.34,1:12:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I got insurance.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.34,1:12:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not blow the whole afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.34,1:12:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm sorry it happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.34,1:12:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That instantly cools down the other person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.43,1:12:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so being graceful towards life in all of its expressions, and people have the right
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.14,1:12:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.14,1:12:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be killed for it, but, I mean, they have the right to be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.83,1:13:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So being gracious towards life means people have differing opinions about things.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.83,1:13:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to get up in arms over every insult.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.90,1:13:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You get used to insults.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.90,1:13:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, you find insults are very amusing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.09,1:13:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And there have been insulting blogs written about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.09,1:13:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, I think they're hysterically funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.09,1:13:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who wrote them seems a little retarded, but they're apparently .
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.09,1:13:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If they think that's funny, I'd say, yeah, with an IQ of, what, 80, that's funny, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.09,1:13:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,An IQ over 100, you wouldn't think it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.09,1:13:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.63,1:13:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity for gratitude and thankfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.63,1:13:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, thank God it's only a dented fender.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.63,1:13:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God it's only a dented fender.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.63,1:13:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're both okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.63,1:13:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're both alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.63,1:13:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither one of us got injured.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.63,1:13:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.63,1:13:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're always choosing the high road.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.63,1:13:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're always choosing mercy instead of revenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.63,1:14:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you could get mad at the guy and give him a good poke in the jaw and justify
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.63,1:14:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that he deserved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.63,1:14:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch put his damn lights on and I smacked into him.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.63,1:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.63,1:14:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You could get him in the car and give him a punch in the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.85,1:14:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one way of living.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.85,1:14:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not putting it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.98,1:14:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying there's anything wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.64,1:14:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But the value of human life is such that you value the other person's life as well as your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.64,1:14:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you value life itself, then its various expressions are acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.74,1:14:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that civilizations rise and fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.09,1:14:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Western civilization is in a free fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.09,1:14:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of America is in free fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.25,1:14:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's okay with you because over history great civilizations have risen and then they've declined.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.50,1:14:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And they've risen and they've declined.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.50,1:15:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So right now we're in a decline.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.79,1:15:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And in free fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.11,1:15:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say well that's the way it's been since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.27,1:15:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.27,1:15:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Great Britain in the early days.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.27,1:15:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the era of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.10,1:15:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.10,1:15:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the great civilizations have risen and they've also fallen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.10,1:15:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So with acceptance then.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.17,1:15:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,With acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.17,1:15:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You accept that all such things tend to fluctuate.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.17,1:15:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we know why?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.19,1:15:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.19,1:15:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.19,1:15:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you know why.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.19,1:15:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.19,1:15:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All I know is that the waves tend to come and go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.19,1:15:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And while we thought it was going to a number of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.26,1:15:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the consciousness level of mankind is just going to keep going right up through the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.26,1:15:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then whoops.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.26,1:15:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden it turned and went down again.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.48,1:15:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Went down again.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.48,1:15:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.48,1:15:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the air gets too rarefied.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.48,1:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People can't handle it or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.64,1:16:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.64,1:16:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Capacity for gratitude and thankfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.64,1:16:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And choosing to be merciful instead of revenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.64,1:16:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Choosing to be merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.64,1:16:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this because we value all of human life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.40,1:16:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are very aware that we are mortal and limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.40,1:16:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness that we're mortal and limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.43,1:16:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mortal.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.43,1:16:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mortal means that the days that are numbered for the survival of the physicality, the body itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.62,1:16:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,From the dust we arise and from dust we return.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.66,1:16:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,From dust we arise and from dust we return.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.75,1:16:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the earlier we accept the inevitability of mortality.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.85,1:16:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The lesser our overall level of anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.85,1:16:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all fears and anxieties are basically the fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.85,1:16:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take any track.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.88,1:16:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If nobody likes me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.88,1:16:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.88,1:16:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.88,1:16:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.88,1:16:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I won't have a job.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.88,1:16:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I won't have any companionship.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.88,1:17:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you keep following every and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.07,1:17:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.07,1:17:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.07,1:17:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Under every fear you'll end up fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.07,1:17:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.30,1:17:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be friendless.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.30,1:17:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I won't have a job.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.30,1:17:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be poor.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.30,1:17:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.39,1:17:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.39,1:17:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you picture the worst possible scenario.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.39,1:17:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And accept the worst possible scenario.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.39,1:17:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then up will come the next worst possible scenario.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.52,1:17:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you get to the very bottom of it is death itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.52,1:17:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to undo any fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.84,1:17:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is to just keep letting go.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.84,1:17:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.84,1:17:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep letting go.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.84,1:17:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.84,1:17:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they'll put me away.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.12,1:17:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.12,1:17:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be lonely.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.12,1:17:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.12,1:17:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll go into despair.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.12,1:17:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.12,1:17:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll stop eating.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.12,1:17:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.12,1:17:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they'll force feed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.12,1:17:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.12,1:17:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.98,1:18:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom of every stack of fear is and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.43,1:18:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you keep going.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.85,1:18:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So anybody here stuck with a stack of fear?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.85,1:18:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody still got a big stack?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.85,1:18:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're working through a big stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.91,1:18:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.91,1:18:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You start from the top of the stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.91,1:18:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.91,1:18:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you recontextualize the and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.91,1:18:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.91,1:18:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So your hair got all frizzled and you're ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.91,1:18:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.91,1:18:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.91,1:18:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll wear a hat.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.91,1:18:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody will notice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.91,1:18:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.91,1:18:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't think it's funny I'm wearing a hat at the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.91,1:18:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.91,1:18:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they will socially reject me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.91,1:18:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.91,1:18:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.91,1:18:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they won't invite me to any more parties.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.91,1:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.91,1:18:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I won't have any friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.91,1:18:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.91,1:18:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you keep going down the and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.01,1:18:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally undo a deep stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.20,1:18:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And all stacks on fear end up at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.20,1:18:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep working on the stack that you'll be unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.23,1:18:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll become a pariah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.52,1:19:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually you'll be left all alone to starve.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.87,1:19:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody will care about you because you're not lovable.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.87,1:19:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore you're going to end up dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.32,1:19:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to save yourself a lot of anxiety
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.90,1:19:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lot of working through negative thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.90,1:19:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and feelings is to accept death.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.90,1:19:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Work your way down the stack and accept that now.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.90,1:19:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you accept that now, the rest of the fears diminish
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.18,1:19:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or disappear altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.18,1:19:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen if we have an atomic war?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.50,1:19:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen if we have an atomic war?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.76,1:19:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then maybe you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.02,1:19:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get that over in one shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.46,1:19:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this lifetime will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.02,1:19:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This physicality will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.02,1:19:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Life will not come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.02,1:19:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Life will not come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.02,1:19:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This physicality will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.02,1:19:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.02,1:20:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So that opens the door for a new life,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.09,1:20:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which is probably going to be better than this one anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.86,1:20:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sooner you get rid of this one,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.86,1:20:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the better you can get on with a better one.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.86,1:20:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'll come back rich and good-looking.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.21,1:20:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance of mortality and limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.53,1:20:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance of mortality and limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.53,1:20:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Death's door.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.53,1:20:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've told you about my own inner experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.78,1:20:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of letting go and surrendering everything
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.78,1:20:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,until I came to there was nothing left,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.20,1:20:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing left to surrender to God, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.42,1:20:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.42,1:20:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything was silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.42,1:20:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came the awareness out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.06,1:20:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I had not surrendered my life to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.75,1:20:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd surrendered everything else, but not life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.14,1:20:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.81,1:21:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This, too, must be surrendered to the ill Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.81,1:21:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd surrendered joy, ecstasy, peace, serenity,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.97,1:21:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of things to the ill Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.97,1:21:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All was gone, and all was silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.67,1:21:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in a very high space.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.67,1:21:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no one there, no other entities,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.74,1:21:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,no other entities.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.74,1:21:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the highest spaces, there are no other entities
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.02,1:21:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to you or giving you instructions
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.02,1:21:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or giving you dictations.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.02,1:21:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.60,1:21:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing but the knowingness that came out of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.66,1:21:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,came out of the frequency and the vibration
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.66,1:21:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of some great guru in past lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.66,1:21:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness that that which I am
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.70,1:21:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond life and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.14,1:21:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the clinging to life was the last thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.14,1:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.14,1:21:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the tenacity of hanging on to life,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.05,1:21:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrendered life.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.40,1:22:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.40,1:22:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Came the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.40,1:22:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.40,1:22:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.46,1:22:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.46,1:22:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the voice of the teacher that radiates forth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.46,1:22:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from the aura has to be, has to come from absolutism.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.82,1:22:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot come from relativism or thinkingism.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.82,1:22:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to come from the absolutism of absolute knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.82,1:22:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of having been there and done that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.14,1:22:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the absolutism of the knowingness that it was,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.14,1:22:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that this too I would surrender to thee, O Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.46,1:22:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrendered life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.46,1:22:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.46,1:22:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has ever, you never surrender life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.22,1:22:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Lifetime after lifetime you don't surrender the source of life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.22,1:22:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the very core,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.35,1:22:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the very core of the narcissistic core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.35,1:22:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that thinks it is the author of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.42,1:22:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the center and the core of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.42,1:23:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So in surrendering what the mind has believed for eons of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.45,1:23:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,up came a great terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.45,1:23:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Up came a great terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.54,1:23:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A severe terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.14,1:23:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And fortunately it only lasted for a few moments.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.14,1:23:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a great terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.14,1:23:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tell you now, number one, it's safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.14,1:23:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Number two, then up will come a great terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.14,1:23:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And surrender to the terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.98,1:23:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the terror disappeared and the fear gone forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.59,1:23:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear which had been there forever
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.66,1:23:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,was now gone forever, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.17,1:23:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mortality then is first the mortality of the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.17,1:23:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this particular incarnation, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.71,1:23:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually as you keep letting go of things,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.71,1:23:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the fears all disappear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.71,1:23:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.32,1:23:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so whatever happens to you is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.38,1:23:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, why is it irrelevant?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.38,1:24:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's God's problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.86,1:24:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If this ceiling falls on us all now,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.86,1:24:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's God's problem, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.86,1:24:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to just sit and wait
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.86,1:24:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what God's going to do about it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.86,1:24:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'll get a truck or a derrick here or ambulances.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.86,1:24:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you won't, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.11,1:24:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'll breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.11,1:24:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.11,1:24:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they'll give you a tank of oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.11,1:24:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they'll say he looks like he's a goner.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.26,1:24:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear the people say, he's a goner.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.26,1:24:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.33,1:24:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a goner.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.33,1:24:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.62,1:24:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.68,1:24:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's your Blue Cross card, boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.13,1:24:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a karmic Blue Cross card.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.13,1:24:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see your card.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.13,1:24:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.19,1:24:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get a few more breaths.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.19,1:25:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a few more breaths left on his Blue Cross card.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.19,1:25:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.19,1:25:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Give him a little oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.50,1:25:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.50,1:25:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens then?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.50,1:25:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to come back to this particular life again.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.50,1:25:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.70,1:25:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the acceptance then of mortality as an inevitability
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.70,1:25:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting over the fear of it the earlier in life we start.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.92,1:25:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is only a matter of acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.92,1:25:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As I pointed out, you know, about to get blown sky high with a mine
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.92,1:25:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.92,1:25:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it was, you know, I said to him, so he dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.92,1:25:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, yeah, right, so you die.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.18,1:25:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.18,1:25:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fear of death is what makes this seem awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.18,1:25:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're struggling with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.18,1:25:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you accept it, it's not awful at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.21,1:25:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you blow up, so what?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.40,1:25:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you blow up.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.40,1:25:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Big deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.36,1:25:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.36,1:25:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.36,1:25:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If we all blow up right now, what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.36,1:25:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We all go together?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.47,1:25:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Foof.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.08,1:26:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no such luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.87,1:26:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One reason people have a fear of dying is because of moral accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.93,1:26:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.93,1:26:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.22,1:26:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason they don't want to die is because they know they're going to be faced
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.22,1:26:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with a moral accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.22,1:26:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One's angel takes a moral inventory with you in which you get a chance to look at yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.53,1:26:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.53,1:26:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole life runs before you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.69,1:26:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole life runs before you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.69,1:26:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole life runs before you at the last moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.98,1:26:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And one is accompanied by an angel at this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.26,1:26:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.38,1:26:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One is accompanied by one special angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.38,1:26:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.66,1:27:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One is accompanied by a divine angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.01,1:27:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One's guardian angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.07,1:27:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you take the moral inventory as you exit,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.07,1:27:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't take it alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.07,1:27:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You take it along with your own guardian angel who reviews your life with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.07,1:27:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see the options and the choices and the karmic energies for the next reincarnation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.07,1:27:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are already set.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.07,1:27:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you see yourself as you really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.52,1:27:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I don't want that to be on my soul forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.52,1:27:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.52,1:27:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want that unkindness.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.71,1:27:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want that negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.71,1:27:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want that selfishness to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.71,1:27:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I beg for a chance to correct that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.74,1:28:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, if you're karmically entitled, you get a chance to reincarnate.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.74,1:28:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time, you're going to be more sympathetic, more understanding, more forgiving, more loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.74,1:28:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to value life above winning.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.74,1:28:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the moral accountability is why most people are afraid to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.45,1:28:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you realize that you're about to get confronted with the truth of what you have been.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.45,1:28:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.51,1:28:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we accept moral accountability as we go through life, we don't build up a fear about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.51,1:28:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we pray for forgiveness for, you know, I was very short and not very sympathetic.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.51,1:28:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forgive myself for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.51,1:28:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I ask God to help me to become more gracious, more gracious.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.51,1:28:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So moral accountability, then, is one of the reasons that people fear death.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.54,1:28:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.77,1:28:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, at this point, you see your concepts, your beliefs of division.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.77,1:29:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Beliefs of divinity come forth as part of your moral accountability and part of your fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.77,1:29:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you picture God as merciful or punitive will make a big difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.21,1:29:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you picture God as merciful, all-merciful, or angry and punitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.50,1:29:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the anthropomorphic God, as we say, arises out of man's lack of understanding of nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.62,1:29:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he pictures a punitive God who punishes you with earthquakes and volcanoes and things like this because he's angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.88,1:29:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you get beyond the angry God to the God that God is the source of infinite mercy, then your fear of death dissolves.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.88,1:29:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you grow spiritually, you can see that the fear of death lessens and lessens because you picture God as merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.88,1:29:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize on your deathbed you're going to have a companion.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.88,1:29:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that you're going to be given a chance to undo it if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.88,1:30:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to be forced into having another human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.88,1:30:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by your own option.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.88,1:30:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.61,1:30:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You only reincarnate by your own say-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.18,1:30:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only your own option.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.31,1:30:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You only come back if you decide to come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.66,1:30:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to shove you out of the wagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.47,1:30:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to dump you in the dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.18,1:30:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.18,1:30:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to get off the bus here and go around again?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.18,1:30:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, yep, yep, yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.18,1:30:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.18,1:30:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I want to correct the record.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.18,1:30:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to correct the record because you see how long the implication is of that record.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.18,1:30:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A few eons.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.18,1:30:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.18,1:30:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, you get what an eon means.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.18,1:30:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I think I'll correct that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.84,1:31:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, eons are staggeringly horrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.84,1:31:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Eons are horrible beyond all description.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.61,1:31:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the most extreme of the highest points that I've ever experienced,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.61,1:31:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the lowest were also beyond comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.61,1:31:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell is not something, as I've said before in these classes,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.70,1:31:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to flirt with and play with.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.70,1:31:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wickedness and evil are not things that you want to play games with
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.70,1:31:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because the downside of moral consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.78,1:31:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of moral accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.78,1:31:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The concept of divinity is merciful or punitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.80,1:31:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the experience of hell was not inflicted from without.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.82,1:32:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was that the spirit had died to this level.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.98,1:32:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this particular spirit was going to see it through.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.46,1:32:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,See it through.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.52,1:32:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And keep going to explore the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.78,1:32:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the depths of hell is not something anyone wants to experience
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.32,1:32:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even for a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.32,1:32:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, you can't experience it for a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.58,1:32:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Each second is experientially an eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.61,1:32:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So to choose between heaven and hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.61,1:32:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these things, one thing takes you closer to heaven,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.61,1:32:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next decision takes you closer to hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.61,1:32:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, if you become spiritually very advanced,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.61,1:32:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that taking the chance is not worth taking the chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.67,1:32:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a temporary gain to vanity and controlling others
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.67,1:32:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting even and revenge and, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.67,1:32:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a short chuckle as you punch somebody in the mouth
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.99,1:33:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who deserved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.05,1:33:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they do deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.05,1:33:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the moral accountability then takes you to the choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.88,1:33:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a choice between two doors.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.88,1:33:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One door leads to heaven and the other door leads to hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.88,1:33:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the door to hell is awful indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.91,1:33:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So moral accountability, concepts of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.91,1:33:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,whether God is merciful or punitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.91,1:33:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that God does not throw you into hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.30,1:33:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You yourself, by your own choices,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.33,1:33:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,have brought you to that state of abject despair and hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.33,1:33:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the limits of freedom?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.03,1:33:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, there aren't any, are there?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.03,1:33:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any limits to freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.03,1:33:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose to hate God.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.03,1:33:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose to love God.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.03,1:33:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose to be generous.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.03,1:33:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose to be stingy.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.03,1:33:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the limits of freedom?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.03,1:33:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the capacity of the human mind to see what the options are.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.03,1:34:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to see the options.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.03,1:34:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're grasping or you're generous,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.22,1:34:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,flexibility, capacity to learn, to grow, to mature.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.58,1:34:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So most normal people say,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.58,1:34:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I think what I'll do is I'll try to learn from this experience
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.93,1:34:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that that is not the way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.93,1:34:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try and make every part of life subservient,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.93,1:34:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,growing and maturing and developing spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.93,1:34:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an innate energy to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.44,1:34:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called the Lente Vitalis.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.44,1:34:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And it really means, it's a French term meaning,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.63,1:34:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,one's life energy, one's life energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.82,1:34:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That energy flows through you as a certain energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.82,1:34:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Life flows as an energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.82,1:34:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You lend vital.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.82,1:34:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.14,1:35:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, man pictures himself versus the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.14,1:35:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,versus the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.14,1:35:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Man pictures himself as he's thrown into the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.14,1:35:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as an accident of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.14,1:35:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as an evolutionary high point in evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.14,1:35:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Man pictures himself as the evolutionary,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.14,1:35:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,highest evolutionary form on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.14,1:35:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not consider anything higher than himself in this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.14,1:35:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,From this realm, the next level up is the angelic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.14,1:35:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.21,1:35:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The next level up is that of the angelic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.27,1:35:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanness, the next level of your evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.27,1:35:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the non-linear is the angelic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.27,1:35:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you leave the ranks of the bodily humanness,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.37,1:35:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get to be a junior angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.98,1:35:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,An angel in residence.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.98,1:36:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,An angel in learning, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.98,1:36:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be like a resident angel in training.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.98,1:36:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get to be a junior angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.33,1:36:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's ranks of angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.33,1:36:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask these questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.06,1:36:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There are ranks of angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.25,1:36:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There are ranks of angelic beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.25,1:36:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a relief, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.44,1:36:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.50,1:36:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It reaches a certain point,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.50,1:36:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at which point the physical body is now a detriment.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.50,1:36:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's served its learning purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.50,1:36:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it's run its course,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.56,1:36:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it runs out of this vital energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.56,1:36:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you allow it to fall over,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.56,1:36:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and you look at the body laying there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.69,1:36:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if anybody's been...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.69,1:36:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already asked this before.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.69,1:36:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people here have been out of body, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.69,1:36:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people here have been out of body, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.85,1:36:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, when you're out of body,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.85,1:36:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.85,1:36:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you were willing to give your life for this thing here.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.85,1:36:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at this body laying there on the stretcher
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.85,1:37:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or the bed or the rug or the road or wherever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.88,1:37:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell you, it is absolutely not interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.88,1:37:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not attractive.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.88,1:37:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't identify with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.88,1:37:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even think it's mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.88,1:37:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks familiar.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.94,1:37:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The physiognomy, the face looks familiar.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.94,1:37:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectually, you're aware that was your body.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.94,1:37:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has no attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.00,1:37:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no desire to reenergize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.00,1:37:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you say those who've been out of body
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.22,1:37:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,have had a similar experience?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.22,1:37:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no, like, panic or terrible desire
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.44,1:37:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to get back in there and get that thing going again?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.44,1:37:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody remember that?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.95,1:37:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got a volunteer answer?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.95,1:37:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody? Yeah, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.95,1:37:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody had their hand up.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.74,1:37:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the experience like?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.74,1:37:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You were just watching it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.82,1:37:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that peculiar?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.82,1:37:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even identify with the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.82,1:38:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you spend all this money getting haircuts,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.70,1:38:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,$400 haircuts, $400 dental bills,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.86,1:38:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all these procedures and all the time and attention
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.86,1:38:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you lavish on this thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.86,1:38:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it lays there like a lump.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.86,1:38:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally uninteresting.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.89,1:38:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.89,1:38:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had to go back in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.89,1:38:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget where I had to go back in it,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.98,1:38:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that particular trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.98,1:38:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had to go back in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.98,1:38:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was part of my agreement or what.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.98,1:38:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I remember I went back in the body
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.98,1:38:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I ducked backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.98,1:38:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got in the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.98,1:38:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I looked out of the back of my physical head
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.98,1:38:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was the floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.98,1:38:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to back out of my spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.98,1:38:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to back out of the physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.98,1:38:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and go back in the body this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.98,1:38:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was looking up at the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.50,1:38:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.75,1:38:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you're willing to die
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.75,1:39:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and give up everything for this wonderful thing
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.75,1:39:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,called you,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.75,1:39:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which you identify as the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.75,1:39:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you're out of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.94,1:39:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't give you five bucks for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.94,1:39:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.11,1:39:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.11,1:39:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You looked in poor shape besides.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.11,1:39:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I looked at him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.11,1:39:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,God, he looks in pretty bummed out shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.11,1:39:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he was pretty sick
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.11,1:39:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and lying there in the sick bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.30,1:39:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I had never gone back at all,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.30,1:39:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.30,1:39:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But the neat part about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.50,1:39:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is that what you consider to be you
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.50,1:39:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,continues on unabated.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.50,1:39:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that the you, its location
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.50,1:39:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and identification with the body disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.50,1:39:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that what you call you
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.50,1:39:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is sort of like an etheric energy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.50,1:39:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can go anywhere it wants in space.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.50,1:39:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It can go up to the ceiling
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.50,1:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or sit on the window sill.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.50,1:39:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It can do whatever it wants.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.50,1:39:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But the physicality is boring at that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.66,1:39:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so man, pictures,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.66,1:40:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,his relationship to the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.66,1:40:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,his karmic inheritance, his propensities,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.26,1:40:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is not well understood in the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.26,1:40:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What is meant by a karmic inheritance?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.26,1:40:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the energy field of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.97,1:40:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,imprints all your decisions and their consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.97,1:40:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And this etheric body then is your soul,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.97,1:40:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your spirit, it stays with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.97,1:40:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it's context,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.00,1:40:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it tends to influence the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.00,1:40:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of various things happening in your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.00,1:40:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't cause them,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.00,1:40:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but it increases the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.10,1:40:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of collapsing the wave function
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.10,1:40:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from potentiality to actuality of certain events.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.10,1:40:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll say to people,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.13,1:40:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have unfortunate things happening in your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.13,1:40:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if they continue,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.13,1:40:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then look for the karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.13,1:40:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive yourself for being the one
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.13,1:40:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who did that to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.13,1:41:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If animals bite you all the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.13,1:41:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then forgive yourself for having been
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.13,1:41:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,vicious and cruel to animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.13,1:41:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Presume that this is payback.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.51,1:41:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic inheritance and presume that anything
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.77,1:41:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that negative happens to you
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.77,1:41:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.77,1:41:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a matter of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.83,1:41:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a matter of arguing with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.83,1:41:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a likely presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.83,1:41:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if it's a very good presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.83,1:41:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.83,1:41:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a likely presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.18,1:41:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably over 90%.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.25,1:41:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably over 90%, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.25,1:41:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's other karmic propensities
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.25,1:41:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do with race and color and various others.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.25,1:41:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But personal karmic,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.31,1:41:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so if something keeps happening to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.31,1:41:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody hates you,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.31,1:41:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's very painful,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.31,1:41:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,then you've got to find the one
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.31,1:41:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who hates others,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.31,1:41:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.31,1:41:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can't remember it personally
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.60,1:41:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean it doesn't exist
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.60,1:41:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can buy into
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.60,1:41:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.60,1:42:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung described, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.60,1:42:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.60,1:42:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of the collective consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.60,1:42:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've had some things happen in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.60,1:42:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had any, in fact recently,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.60,1:42:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no memory of having any belief
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.60,1:42:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in that possibility whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.60,1:42:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I never gave it the slightest energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.60,1:42:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get osteoporosis?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.60,1:42:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.60,1:42:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought a little old bent over ladies get that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.60,1:42:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I never thought of
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.60,1:42:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a good looking middle aged gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.66,1:42:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,having such a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.66,1:42:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, what is the purpose of human life?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.76,1:42:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, all these questions arise.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.76,1:42:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because how you answer these existential things,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.76,1:42:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they seem abstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.76,1:42:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is how you answer these,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.76,1:42:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which look like a generality,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.76,1:42:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that defines how you choose the particulars.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.76,1:42:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The value of human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.76,1:42:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.89,1:42:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, in my view,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.89,1:42:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of human life is,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.89,1:43:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when we started this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.89,1:43:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve God, to serve humanity,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.89,1:43:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and to serve yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.89,1:43:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To serve yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.18,1:43:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and to serve God by serving yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.18,1:43:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and to serve your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.81,1:43:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fulfill your obligation and your destiny
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.81,1:43:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.97,1:43:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To serve God, self, and your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.97,1:43:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Having done that,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.06,1:43:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is there anything left for you to think of to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.06,1:43:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That pretty much clears off the desk, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.51,1:43:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done all you can to serve God,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.86,1:43:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve your obligation to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.22,1:43:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to move from self for the smallest
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.22,1:43:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to self for the largest,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.60,1:43:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.60,1:43:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby serve God.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.60,1:43:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a channel of God's will,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.60,1:43:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for the good of all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.76,1:43:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as your own evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.76,1:43:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because after all,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.05,1:44:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you are part of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.05,1:44:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so don't leave yourself out.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.72,1:44:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You versus mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.72,1:44:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you are part of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.72,1:44:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So in serving mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.72,1:44:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you serve yourself as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.00,1:44:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of human life then,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.00,1:44:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's what it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.00,1:44:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fulfillment of one's destiny,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.00,1:44:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you fulfill that by service to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.00,1:44:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,God, and fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.06,1:44:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The society you grow up in,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.25,1:44:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,power versus force,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.25,1:44:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,was the first book we wrote on this.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.25,1:44:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Power, which is context,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.25,1:44:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and force, which is linear and Newtonian.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.25,1:44:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between truth versus,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.31,1:44:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.11,1:44:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is now,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.11,1:44:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a quality,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.11,1:44:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of an emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.11,1:44:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, people think of love,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.11,1:44:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,oh baby Ken, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.14,1:44:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is a way of defining one's own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.14,1:44:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.14,1:44:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of lovingness
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.14,1:44:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that you step over the black beetle,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.14,1:45:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because you appreciate the gift of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.14,1:45:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is his only chance,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.14,1:45:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to get this life,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.14,1:45:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't want to bring it,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.14,1:45:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because love is valuable.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.17,1:45:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Love of quality,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.17,1:45:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.17,1:45:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.20,1:45:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said earlier,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.20,1:45:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,affects brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.20,1:45:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How you see and experience the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.20,1:45:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is reflected in your brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.52,1:45:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The childhood experiences then,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.52,1:45:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are the beginning of building of these stacks,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.52,1:45:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and as parents,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.52,1:45:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring all the beauty,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.52,1:45:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,music,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.52,1:45:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual qualities we can.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.52,1:45:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these end up as cultural norms and mores,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.68,1:45:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not people believe in it or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.68,1:45:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, well I don't believe in ethics,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.68,1:45:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and morality,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.68,1:45:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and God,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.68,1:45:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and religion,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.68,1:45:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that 1950s crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.81,1:45:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And all they're reciting now,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.81,1:45:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is what has become a cultural norm,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.81,1:45:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mores of our current day.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.81,1:46:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The mental impact and programming that goes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.93,1:46:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we've already spoken about.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.93,1:46:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this is advanced by technology,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.93,1:46:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the effective forms of communication we have.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.93,1:46:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Access now to vast accumulations of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.15,1:46:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of all of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.38,1:46:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from the house of mirrors,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.38,1:46:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we eventually learn how to sort the wheat from the shaft.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.38,1:46:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And get rid of opinion,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.63,1:46:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissism,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.63,1:46:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.63,1:46:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.63,1:46:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,develop goals and ego ideals,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.63,1:46:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that which we wish to become.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.63,1:46:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.02,1:46:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to identify with the models of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.02,1:46:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Society needs heroes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.02,1:46:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Society needs models.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.14,1:46:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I believe in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.14,1:46:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I used to be a comedian.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.46,1:46:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to be one of the biggest.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.98,1:46:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Cosby, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.98,1:46:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Bill Cosby, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.07,1:46:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And Bill, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.07,1:46:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,does that mentoring.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.07,1:46:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I believe strongly in mentoring.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.07,1:47:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us becomes a mentor,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.07,1:47:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to those who are following behind us.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.07,1:47:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And is that...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.13,1:47:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.13,1:47:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, it's almost time to stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.19,1:47:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anybody have a final question?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.19,1:47:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll come to a stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.82,1:47:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure it's brilliant, intelligent,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.82,1:47:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,worthy of being recorded throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.66,1:47:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.69,1:47:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,God is going to be looking at this
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.69,1:47:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on his computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.36,1:47:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Peter, you know, has a computer now.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.36,1:47:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have an ID number.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.36,1:47:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.54,1:47:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.23,1:47:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don't experience the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.23,1:47:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience your experience of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.23,1:47:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're experiencing is your own experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.35,1:47:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So that comes out of some previous lectures we had.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.35,1:47:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're never experiencing what you think you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.35,1:48:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only experiencing your experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.35,1:48:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're short-circuiting the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.83,1:48:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the time, what you're witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.31,1:48:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,your thoughts, your feelings, your images, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.31,1:48:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is that advanced edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.41,1:48:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, which I call the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.41,1:48:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the experiencer dissolves,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.73,1:48:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no me and the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.73,1:48:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no duality of me and the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.18,1:48:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They are one and the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.97,1:48:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,See, there's no me and the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.97,1:48:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like you don't have a TV screen at Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.10,1:48:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're on Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.41,1:48:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.41,1:48:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reality then is beyond the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.41,1:48:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a 100th second,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.47,1:48:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a second delay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.47,1:48:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always compare it to
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.47,1:48:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the playing back from the monitor of a recording,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.47,1:48:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the old videotape.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.47,1:49:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think they even use them anymore,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.47,1:49:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's on the machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.47,1:49:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.47,1:49:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you push record,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.50,1:49:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you can plug into the monitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.70,1:49:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what you're getting is the monitor playback
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.92,1:49:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the direct experience of the reality of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.92,1:49:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which is that you don't have to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.73,1:49:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.73,1:49:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So then what happens now?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.62,1:49:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have a brief break?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.62,1:49:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a 15-minute break.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.62,1:49:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,15-minute break.
